  abstract = {A Monte Carlo simulation model based on Geant4 toolkit has been developed to simulate the production of heavy-nuclei recoils and their trajectories through the gas-filled recoil separator SHANS2 (Spectrometer for Heavy Atoms and Nuclear Structure-2). Methods of the simulation model are presented and several physics processes were implemented in Geant4. A set of average charge states of heavy ions measured at SHANS2 in helium gas are presented and a new empirical formula based on the experimental data was derived to describe the charge-exchange process. The simulated results for the focal plane image size of recoils, magnetic rigidity dispersion, and transmission efficiency were compared with the data obtained in 169Tm(40Ar, 4-5n)204,205Fr and 208Pb(48Ca, 2n)254No reactions. Good agreement between simulation and experimental results is found, which allows us to use the model for tuning the separator in future experiments aimed at investigations of the heaviest nuclei.},
